OL,6,FIn the second case, WJEC reported that
OL,7,Fit had allowed nearly 4,000 exam
OL,8,Fpapers between 2017 and 2023 to be
OL,9,Freviewed by the same assessors who had
OL,10,Foriginally marked at least part of
OL,11,Fthem, which broke exam regulations.
OL,13,FIn response to the incident, WJEC said
OL,14,Fit "sincerely" apologises and takes
OL,15,F"full responsibility."
OL,17,FIt has issued credit notes as
OL,18,Ffinancial compensation to schools and
OL,19,Fcolleges affected, totalling just over
OL,20,F#219,000.
